  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "```\r\nbool a = true;\r\nbool b = false;\r\nbool c;\r\n\r\n// compiles\r\nc = a < b;\r\nc = a <= b;\r\nc = a > b;\r\nc = a >= b;\r\n\r\n// rejected\r\nc = a | b; // bitwise or\r\nc = a ^ b; // bitwise xor\r\nc = a & b; // bitwise and\r\nc = a << b; // shifts (all of them are properly rejected)\r\n// add, sub, mul, div, mod and exp is rejected\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnly logical `and` and `or` and (non)equality should be supported.\r\n\r\nFound by @leonardoalt.",
